  "title": "Associate Trainer (Cleaning | Corporate Clients | Revenue Share)",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p>We are seeking an experienced <strong>Associate Trainer</strong> with an <strong>existing</strong> <strong>network</strong> of cleaning or Integrated Facilities Management (IFM) companies to deliver our <strong>PWM WSQ Cleaning courses</strong>. <br /><br />You are the lead for corporate clients originated by you, and deliver training, while being fully supported by Adepco’s administrative, marketing, and compliance systems.<br /><br />This role is suited for trainers or industry practitioners who want <strong>income upside, autonomy, accounts ownership and a long-term 2-way partnership with us</strong>.</p><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><h3><strong>Corporate & Business Development (Primary)</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Leverage <strong>your</strong> <strong>existing network</strong> of cleaning or IFM companies to generate corporate training engagements</p></li><li><p>Identify client <strong>training</strong> needs aligned with PWM, NEA licensing, and WSQ requirements</p></li><li><p>Act as the primary <strong>liaison</strong> for assigned corporate clients</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with Adepco on training schedules </p></li></ul><h3><strong>Training Delivery (Secondary)</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Deliver our PWM WSQ Cleaning modules </p></li><li><p>Conduct training at client sites, classrooms, food courts, dormitories, or workplaces as required by your clients</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Compliance & Professional Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Comply with Adepco and SkillsFuture Singapore (SSG) processes and SOPs</p></li><li><p>Provide timely updates on attendance, absentees, assessments and issues</p></li><li><p>Participate in trainer briefings and annual reviews</p></li></ul><h2><strong>What We Provide</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Full administrative, billing, funding, and compliance support</p></li><li><p>WSQ-accredited courses with approved curriculum and materials</p></li><li><p>Strong brand credibility as a <strong>TPQA Grade 1 Training Provider</strong></p></li><li><p>Centralised coordination for scheduling, invoicing, and certificate issuance</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Compensation & Benefits</strong></h2><ul><li><p><strong>Training revenue share</strong> from corporate clients originated and managed by you under Adepco </p></li><li><p><strong>Trainer fees</strong> for course delivery</p></li><li><p>Flexible engagement model (associate / freelance basis)</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>ACTA or ACLP certification</p></li><li><p>Established network within cleaning, facilities management, or related sectors</p></li><li><p>Strong independence, and professionalism</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Who This Role Is For</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Trainers seeking revenue partnership more than per-run training fees</p></li><li><p>Industry practitioners wanting to leverage on your corporate relationships</p></li><li><p>Looking for <strong>income upside and autonomy</strong>, not limited to training fees</p></li></ul><h3><strong></strong><br /><strong>Industry</strong></h3><p>Education | Training | Environmental Services | Cleaning</p>",
